abstract: A party-line vote blocked documents from the budget office.
lead_paragraph: The Senate turned back a Democratic effort to subpoena White House budget documents for President Trumpâ€™s impeachment trial. The move to table the effort succeeded along party lines, 53 to 47, with Republicans prevailing in the latest in a series of partisan votes to block new evidence demanded by Democrats from coming to light. Republicans had succeeded in tabling two other similar measures.
